1
00:00:01,500 --> 00:00:07,800
Offline OCR — a safe, fully offline region-select OCR.

2
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:13,500
It's incredibly simple to use.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,300
Just drag your mouse over the text you want to OCR.

4
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:27,800
The National Diet Library's OCR technology recognizes text right inside your browser.

5
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:35,200
The result is automatically copied to your clipboard. Ready to paste.

6
00:00:37,700 --> 00:00:44,000
Fully offline. Optimized for Japanese. Supports vertical text. One-click launch.

7
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:49,800
Let's look at the key features.

8
00:00:52,300 --> 00:01:02,500
All processing happens inside your browser. No data is ever sent externally. Powered by a high-accuracy engine developed by the National Diet Library of Japan.

9
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:14,800
Supports both horizontal and vertical Japanese text, including old books. Launch from the toolbar, keyboard shortcut, or right-click menu.

10
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:25,900
Auto-clean OCR results with custom regex rules. The UI automatically switches between Japanese and English.

11
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:34,700
About privacy. This extension never sends your data anywhere.

12
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:45,500
Screenshots, the OCR engine, AI models, and results — everything stays in your browser.

13
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:53,600
Communication with external servers is completely blocked. No images or text are transmitted.

14
00:01:56,100 --> 00:02:04,000
Zero network requests. Zero data collection. It works even without an internet connection.

15
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:10,200
Let's look at the cleaning rules feature.

16
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:25,600
You can auto-format OCR results with regex before copying. Add, reorder, and toggle rules freely.

17
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:34,900
For example, invoice amounts. The raw OCR data contains commas and spaces...

18
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:43,000
Apply the rules, and the result is cleaned up into plain numbers.

19
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:49,000
Here's how it works under the hood.

20
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:58,500
The Content Script displays the selection UI and sends coordinates to the Service Worker.

21
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:06,200
The Service Worker captures a screenshot and forwards it to the OCR Worker.

22
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:13,000
ONNX Runtime Web runs local inference.

23
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:25,400
The result is sent back and written to the clipboard. All running locally on Manifest V3.
